  "system": {
    "itemKey": "",
    "description": "<p>You slam a Grappled creature.</p><p><em><strong>Range:</strong> Melee</em></p><p>Make a Melee Martial Attack against the target’s AD.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Hit:</strong> The target takes 1 Bludgeoning damage.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Maneuver Enhancements</span></strong></span></p><p><strong>Multi-Slam: (1 AP + 1 SP, Repeatable) </strong>This Attack targets another creature you have Grappled.</p><p><strong>Charging Slam: (1 AP + 1 SP, Repeatable)</strong> You move up to your Speed pulling the Grappled creatures with you. 1 Grappled creature takes additional damage equal to the number of Spaces moved as you slam them.</p><p><strong>Wall Rake: (1 AP + 1 SP, Repeatable)</strong> You slam 1 Grappled creature into a wall within 1 Space and move up to your Speed along the wall, ending your movement within 1 Space of the wall. The target makes a Repeated Might Save against your Save DC. <strong>Save Failure:</strong> They gain 1 stack of Bleeding per Space moved.</p><p><strong>DC Tip:</strong> Remember that you are Slowed while Grappling a creature, so you would move half as far. If you gain an ability that let’s you move without being Slowed while Grappling a creature, you could move the full distance.</p>",
